    "created_at": "2016-03-31T05:35:15Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-03-31T05:35:15Z",
    "body": "@zcbenz I can't agree with you that node-webkit's integration of Node is buggy: it integrates the renderer event loop and Node's into the same thread so the function call between the 2 worlds is made directly and efficient. While in Electron is 2 event loops in 2 different threads, when a function call is made from DOM to Node or vice versa, you have to do some thread synchronization thing like pausing one thread, or post the the function call into something like a queue and wait for the other thread to pick it up, which is inefficient.\n"
  },
